Raw dev notes -- UPS Shipping Calculator: React + TypeScript Desktop App (Feb 2026)

Built a shipping cost calculator for UPS Israel. React + TypeScript frontend, packaged as
desktop app. Pulls zone data and pricing from Excel files.

Key work this month:
- Broke down monolithic App.tsx into 6 focused components
- Fixed all 52 TypeScript errors for clean production build
- Added comprehensive vitest test suite (74 tests)
- Built localStorage persistence for form state
- Custom app icon for EXE and favicon
- Fixed tip clarity: combine dual surcharges, add specific weight thresholds
- Pallet warnings redesign
- Surcharge reduction tips made actionable

Struggles:
- ESLint v9 breaking changes during the refactor
- Zone data parser needed caching to avoid redundant fetches
- GitBash + npm output capture is flaky -- had to redirect to temp files

The calculator now handles multi-item shipments with proper dimensional weight,
pallet surcharges, and generates PDF quotes. Tests cover 74 scenarios.
